---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import Button from './Button.astro';
import Icon from './Icon.astro';

const issues = await getCollection('issues');
const totalIssues = issues.length;
---

<section class="bg-white py-16 md:py-24 px-4 md:px-10 bg-pattern-grid">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold title-bar mb-8">
      The archive
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-4 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-dark max-w-[700px]">
      <p>
        Every single issue we ever published is still available. That's {totalIssues} issues you can browse,
        search, and read, with full-text search powered by
        <a href="https://pagefind.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="underline decoration-brand-primary underline-offset-2 hover:text-brand-dark transition-colors">Pagefind</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Take a trip down memory lane: revisit what tech was hot a few years back, see how the web evolved
        over the years, rediscover the trends that shaped frontend and backend development. You might even
        find some hidden gems that are still relevant today.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <Button href="/archive" variant="primary" size="lg">
        <Icon name="archive" size={18} />
        Browse the archive
      </Button>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-neutral-darkest/5 border-l-4 border-brand-primary">
      <h3 class="font-heading text-base font-semibold mb-3">
        Nerd corner: take the data with you
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-dark leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We've made the entire archive available as structured data. Download it, query it, build something cool with it.
        You could even load the Parquet file into <a href="https://duckdb.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline hover:text-brand-dark">DuckDB</a> and
        run SQL queries against almost a decade of fullstack web development trends.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <Button href="/fullstackbulletin-archive.json" variant="secondary" size="sm" download>
          <Icon name="download" size={16} />
          Download JSON
        </Button>
        <Button href="/fullstackbulletin-archive.parquet" variant="secondary" size="sm" download>
          <Icon name="download" size={16} />
          Download Parquet
        </Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
